NEW STATEMENT:

890
Your Worship,

I stand before you today as Charlotte Porter, pleading guilty to the charge of careless driving. I deeply regret the events that transpired on the day in question and acknowledge the seriousness of my actions.

As a 37-year-old individual with an otherwise clean record, I have always strived to be a responsible driver. However, on that fateful day, I made regrettable choices. I was rushing to the airport to pick up my family members and allowed my impatience to lead me into careless driving. I exceeded the speed limit and drove aggressively, endangering myself and others on the road.

Moreover, I acknowledge that I acted negligently by answering a text message from my cousin while behind the wheel. This distraction prevented me from fully focusing on the road, resulting in the collision with the guardrail.

Though I am genuinely remorseful for my actions, I am aware of the potential harm I could have caused not only to myself but also to innocent individuals on the road that day. I understand the gravity of my poor choices and assure the court that I have learned from this experience.

I request the court's consideration of the circumstances surrounding my case, taking into account my previously demonstrated good character. I am an individual who is committed to personal growth and ensuring the safety of myself and others on the road. Additionally, I regularly make donations to the British Heart Foundation as a testament to my dedication to helping others.

I express my sincerest remorse for my irresponsible behavior and thank the court for allowing me the opportunity to take full responsibility for my actions. I assure you that moving forward, I will remain a responsible and law-abiding driver.

Thank you for your time and consideration regarding this matter.

Sincerely,
Charlotte Porter
